1942;;The Hidden Hand;;American;;Benjamin Stoloff;;Craig Stevens, Elisabeth Fraser;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hidden_Hand_(1942_film);;John Channing (Milton Parsons) is as insane-asylum escapee. In her efforts to protect her brother from the authorities, John's sister Lorinda (Cecil Cunningham) opens the door for a series of grisly murders. Peter Thorne (Craig Stevens) and Mary Winfield (Elizabeth Fraser) try to stop John before he kills again.[1]